ts%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-office-new-staff-cuts-federal-workers-responde-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshrink%20the%20federal%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20lawsuit%20is%20just%20one%20of%20several%20pushing%20back%20against%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20stance%20that%20the%20federal%20workforce%20is%20bloated%20and%20inefficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlaintiffs%20argued%20that%20OPM%20had%20no%20legal%20authority%20to%20terminate%20probationary%20employees%2C%20generally%20meaning%20those%20with%20less%20than%20a%20year%20on%20the%20job%2C%20and%20that%20the%20firings%20were%20based%20on%20false%20claims%20of%20poor%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20attorneys%20said%20in%20court%20that%20OPM%20did%20not%20mandate%20the%20firings%20but%20merely%20advised%20agencies%20to%20assess%20whether%20probationary%20employees%20met%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fless-than-half-of-federal-workforce-replied-doge-productivity-email-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20standards%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20argued%20that%20these%20employees%20are%20not%20entitled%20to%20guaranteed%20employment%20and%20that%20federal%20agencies%20should%20prioritize%20retaining%20only%20top-performing%20and%20mission-critical%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlsap%20could%20summon%20Charles%20Ezell%2C%20Acting%20Director%20of%20OPM%2C%20to%20testify%20in%20court%20under%20oath%20in%20March%20about%20his%20communications%20to%20agencies%20regarding%20terminating%20employees.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-orders-federal-workers-associated-with-doge-office-subpoena-lawsuit-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDOGE%20office-affiliated%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20also%20be%20subpoenaed%20to%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20order%20what%20I'm%20about%20to%20say%20because%20we%20don't%20have%20the%20parties%20in%20front%20of%20me%20to%20give%20relief.%20But%20I'm%20going%20to%20count%20on%20the%20government%20to%20do%20the%20right%20thing%20and%20to%20go%20a%20little%20bit%20further%20than%20I%20have%20ordered%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alsap%20shortly%20before%20adjourning%20the%20court%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20to%20let%20some%20of%20these%20agencies%20know%20what%20I%20have%20ruled%20because%20I%20would%20hate%20for%20probationary%20employees%20to%20lose%20their%20job%20and%20for%20the%20government%20to%20be%20compromised.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThis%20ruling%20by%20Judge%20Alsup%20is%20an%20important%20initial%20victory%20for%20patriotic%20Americans%20across%20this%20country%20who%20were%20illegally%20fired%20from%20their%20jobs%20by%20an%20agency%20that%20had%20no%20authority%20to%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Everett%20Kelley%2C%20National%20President%20of%20the%20American%20Federation%20of%20Government%20Employees.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20rank-and-file%20workers%20who%20joined%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20their%20communities%2C%20only%20to%20be%20suddenly%20terminated%20due%20to%20this%20administration's%20disdain%20for%20federal%20employees%20and%20desire%20to%20privatize%20their%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-rules-trump-mass-firings-probationary-federal-employees-invalid-doge-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740705636000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c109d269253ccddf97dd0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-rules-trump-mass-firings-probationary-federal-employees-invalid-doge-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20judge%20ruled%20the%20OPM%20must%20retract%20memos%20calling%20for%20mass%20layoffs%20of%20probationary%20employees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22katherineli%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20Li)%22%2C