nt%20of%20Labor%20on%20February%205%20over%20access%20to%20sensitive%20personal%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20granted%20the%20plaintiffs'%20request%20to%20conduct%20four%20depositions%2C%20one%20each%20with%20the%20agencies%20named%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%2C%20and%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20United%20States%20DOGE%20Service.%20However%2C%20it%20also%20said%20the%20depositions%20would%20be%20capped%20at%20%26quot%3Beight%20hours%20in%20the%20aggregate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20wrote%20that%20%26quot%3Bunderstandably%2C%20defendants%20argue%20most%20strongly%20against%26quot%3B%20the%20depositions.%20But%20he%20said%20the%20depositions%20being%20limited%20to%20specific%20topics%20and%20in%20length%20meant%20they%20did%20not%20pose%20too%20high%20a%20burden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20topics%20that%20can%20be%20discussed%20in%20the%20depositions%20include%20how%20access%20to%20systems%20at%20each%20agency%20changed%20after%20the%20DOGE%20office%20was%20created%2C%20the%20role%20of%20DOGE%20office%20employees%20at%20the%20agencies%2C%20and%20how%20those%20employees%20are%20using%20sensitive%20systems%20at%20the%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20which%20specific%20Trump%20administration%20officials%20would%20be%20asked%20to%20sit%20for%20the%20depositions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20is%20one%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-executive-order-outlines-powers-of-doge-federal-agencies-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2085%20lawsuits%3C%2Fa%3E%20challenging%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20DOGE%20office's%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAFL-CIO%20filed%20a%20motion%20for%20expedited%20discovery%2C%20citing%20limited%20information%20about%20the%20DOGE%20office's%20current%20operation.%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20District%20Judge%20John%20Bates%20wrote%20in%20the%20ruling%20that%20the%20DOGE%20office's%20%26quot%3Bstructure%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bscope%20of%20authority%26quot%3B%20are%20%26quot%3Bnot%20only%20unclear%20on%20the%20current%20record%20but%20also%20critical%26quot%3B%20to%20decide%20how%20the%20law%20applies%20to%20the%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBates%20wrote%20that%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bstrange%20to%20permit%20defendants%20to%20submit%20evidence%20that%20addresses%20critical%20factual%20issues%20and%20proceed%20to%20rule%20on%20a%20preliminary%20injunction%20motion%20without%20permitting%20plaintiffs%20to%20explore%20those%20factual%20issues%20through%20very%20limited%20discovery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%2C%20and%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-orders-federal-workers-associated-with-doge-office-subpoena-lawsuit-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740695305000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0d726b8b41a9673f93ec4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-orders-federal-workers-associated-with-doge-office-subpoena-lawsuit-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20District%20Judge%20John%20Bates%20highlighted%20the%20DOGE%20office's%20%26quot%3Bunclear%26quot%3B%20structure%20and%20authority%20as%20keys%20to%20the%20legal%20decision.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer%2CKelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A190%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-orders-federal-workers-associated-with-doge-office-subpoena-lawsuit-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampU