22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0b982b1834fe31165b0bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22568%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENATO%20said%20its%20new%20drone%20boat%20force%20was%20undergoing%20demonstrations%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea.%3Cp%3ENATO%20Allied%20Command%20Transformation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENew%20NATO%20naval%20drones%20are%20being%20put%20to%20the%20test%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20uncrewed%20surface%20vehicles%20are%20part%20of%20the%20alliance's%20efforts%20to%20deter%20aggression%20and%20sabotage.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20new%20Task%20Force%20X%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20US%20Navy's%20Task%20Force%2059%20efforts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NATO%20alliance%20has%20been%20testing%20new%20Task%20Force%20X%20naval%20drones%20in%20the%20strategic%20waters%20of%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%2C%20showing%20off%20the%20new%20capabilities%20of%20these%20uncrewed%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drones%20are%20intended%20to%20help%20the%20allies%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20Russia's%20activities%20in%20the%20region%20and%20deter%20the%20potential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-west-vital-undersea-cables-are-so-vulnerable-to-attack-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esabotage%20of%20critical%20undersea%20infrastructure%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20data%20cables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20Allied%20Command%20Transformation%20announced%20the%20drone%20demonstrations%20Wednesday%2C%20saying%20they%20%26quot%3Bsignal%20a%20significant%20step%20forward%20in%20integrating%20unmanned%20surface%20vessels%2C%20commonly%20referred%20to%20as%20USVs%2C%20to%20bolster%20NATO's%20ability%20to%20safeguard%20critical%20infrastructure%20and%20maintain%20security%20in%20an%20increasingly%20complex%20environment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrench%20Adm.%20Pierre%20Vandier%2C%20the%20NATO%20Supreme%20Allied%20Commander%20Transformation%2C%20said%20Task%20Force%20X%20will%20fill%20surveillance%20gaps%20in%20the%20region.%20Bart%20Hollants%2C%20an%20official%20from%20NATO's%20Allied%20Command%20Transformation%20Branch%2C%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20tangible%20results%26quot%3B%20of%20NATO's%20efforts%20to%20curb%20security%20threats%20in%20the%20Baltic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demonstration%20involved%20NATO%20maritime%20assets%2C%20including%20from%20the%20Royal%20Danish%20and%20German%20navies%2C%20testing%20how%20drones%20work%20together%20with%20crewed%20vessels.%20The%20testing%20activities%20included%20tactical%20maneuvering%20exercises%20like%20live-fire%20events%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20integrating%20drones%20into%20NATO's%20naval%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20announced%20its%20plans%20to%20establish%20Task%20Force%20X%20and%20employ%20naval%20drones%20in%20late%20January.%20The%20aim%20of%20the%20project%20is%20to%20counter%20and%20deter%20state%20and%20non-state%20actors%20from%20sabotaging%20undersea%20cables%2C%20as%20well%20as%20curb%20potential%20Russian%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETask%20Force%20X%20is%20working%20to%20field%20%26quot%3Ba%20fleet%20of%20maritime%20autonomous%20systems%20to%20provide%20persistent%20surveillance%2C%20detect%20and%20track%20potential%20threats%2C%20and%20enhance%20situational%20awareness%2C%26quot%3B%20NATO%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20approach%20offers%20a%20cost-effective%20and%20rapidly%20deployable%20solution%20to%20counter%20Russian%20aggression.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Models%20of%20drones%20are%20kept%20in%20a%20warehouse%20at%20Naval%20Support%20Activity%20Bahrain.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f99a372417f97b87cd4950%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EModels%20of%20drones%20are%20kept%20in%20a%20warehouse%20at%20Naval%20Support%20Activity%20Bahrain.%3Cp%3EJake%20Epstein%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20came%20after%20several%20incidents%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20which%20undersea%20cables%20in%20the%20Baltic%20were%20damaged%20by%20vessels%20linked%20to%20Russia%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20troubling%20incidents%20were%20suspected%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20being%20part%20of%20Russia's%20ongoing%20hybrid%20and%20irregular%20warfare%20tactics%20against%20Western%20European%20nations%2C%20gray-zone%20tactics%20below%20the%20threshold%20of%20armed%20conflict.%20Other%20recent%20examples%20include%20Russian%20interference%20in%20European%20elections%20and%20misinformation%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcern%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-plan-to-defend-undersea-internet-from-sabotage-using-satellites-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etargeting%20of%20critical%20undersea%20cables%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20related%20infrastructure%20has%20led%20NATO%20to%20take%20action.%20NATO's%20new%20Task%20Force%20X%2C%20the%20alliance%20said%2C%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20US%20Navy's%20Task%20Force%2059%2C%20an%20initiative%20fielding%20naval%20drones%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-us-naval-drone-program-spy-defeat-middle-east-threats-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETask%20Force%2059%20is%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20Navy%20initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%20started%20in%20September%202021.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20task%20force%20has%20conducted%20at%20least%2035%20bilateral%20and%20multilateral%20exercises%2C%20operating%20drones%20at%20sea%20for%20more%20than%2060%2C000%20hours%20across%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20US%20Navy%20and%20NATO's%20efforts%20speak%20to%20the%20growing%20employment%20of%20uncrewed%20systems%20and%2C%20to%20some%20degree%2C%20autonomy%20in%20surveillance%20and%20deterrence%20roles.%20In%20both%20cases%2C%20the%20drones%20are%20intended%20to%20give%20militar