US%20government%2C%20suggested%20Thursday%20that%20members%20of%20the%20US%20Congress%20should%20get%20salary%20increases%20as%20a%20way%20to%20discourage%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20tech%20billionaire%20is%20officially%20only%20an%20advisor%2C%20Trump%20has%20bestowed%20him%20with%20enormous%20power%20to%20cut%20federal%20spending%20and%20bureaucracy%2C%20as%20part%20of%20his%20so-called%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20(DOGE).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20might%20make%20sense%20to%20increase%20compensation%20for%20Congress%20and%20senior%20government%20employees%20to%20reduce%20the%20forcing%20function%20for%20corruption%2C%20as%20the%20latter%20might%20be%20as%20much%20as%201000%20times%20more%20expensive%20to%20the%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20posted%20on%20his%20social%20media%20platform%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawmakers%20in%20both%20parties%20are%20typically%20wary%20of%20the%20optics%20of%20large%20pay%20rises%20but%20acknowledge%20that%20competitive%20salaries%20are%20the%20best%20way%20of%20ensuring%20that%20the%20less%20well-off%20can%20serve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20draft%20of%20a%20short-term%20government%20funding%20bill%20that%20Musk%20helped%20defeat%20in%20December%20would%20have%20allowed%20for%20a%20modest%20salary%20increase%20by%20reenacting%20an%20automatic%20cost-of-living%20adjustment%20for%20lawmakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20has%20been%20blocking%20the%20adjustments%20every%20year%20since%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Musk%20argued%20against%20the%20provision%2C%20claiming%20falsely%20that%20it%20would%20mean%20a%20lavish%2040%20percent%20rise%2C%20and%20it%20was%20removed%20from%20the%20package.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20increase%20for%20members%20of%20both%20chambers%20would%20have%20been%20about%20%246%2C600%2C%20or%203.8%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20%24174%2C000%20annual%20salary%20has%20been%20frozen%20for%2015%20years%20but%20is%20still%20far%20more%20t